First we calculate our μ, just the mean of each column in X:

mu = mean(X, 1)
Having found our mean, we can now calculate the covariance matrix:

function covariance(x, mu)
  n = length(x[:,1])
  (x .- mu)' * (x .- mu) ./ n
end

sigma = covariance(X, mu)



